# AI Workflow
- Always read the `brain.md` file completely before generating any code.
- Always search brain.md for implementation patterns before writing any new API endpoint.
- When requested to create API or API group, any database changes needed, always add to both db.sql and to UpgradeDB.sql and Use all the standard flows defined in brain.md
- When requested to update the brain.md file, always update its Document Version and Last Updated fields.

# Style Guide
- Always use tab of 4 spaces for code indentation.
- Always place curly braces on a new line (Allman style).

# SQL Syntax and Style
- Use 'JOIN' instead of 'INNER JOIN'
- Use 'LEFT OUTER JOIN' instead of 'LEFT JOIN'
- Indent JOINs on a new line in one tab more than the 'FROM' clause
- Don't use table aliases if not needed
- Don't use 'AS' keyword for table aliases
- Don't use 'AS' keyword for column aliases
